&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Anthropic&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anthropic’s mission is to create reliable, interpretable, and steerable AI systems. We want AI to be safe and beneficial for our users and for society as a whole. Our team is a quickly growing group of committed researchers, engineers, policy experts, and business leaders working together to build beneficial AI systems.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;About the role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Corporate Network Engineer on Anthropic&#39;s IT Engineering team, you&#39;ll help establish and expand the network infrastructure that enables our teams to advance AI safety research and development. This is an opportunity to shape the foundation of our corporate network architecture as we scale, building reliable and secure connectivity solutions for our growing global presence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll focus primarily on designing and operating corporate office network infrastructure, creating the physical and wireless environments where our staff collaborate. As we expand our facilities and headcount, your work will directly enable productive, secure workspaces that support both in-person collaboration and hybrid work models.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and implement corporate office network infrastructure from the ground up, including wired and wireless networks, across multiple locations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish network standards, best practices, and architectural patterns that will scale with our rapid growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain high-performance wireless networks that support dense user environments and diverse device requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop automation tools and monitoring solutions to ensure network reliability and rapid issue resolution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Facilities and Security teams to plan and integrate network infrastructure into new office buildouts and expansions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage vendor relationships, oversee circuit procurement, and handle equipment lifecycle planning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create comprehensive documentation, runbooks, and knowledge bases for network operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in an on-call rotation to provide network support and incident response&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement network security controls including segmentation, access control, and guest network isolation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with infrastructure teams to ensure seamless connectivity between office networks and cloud resources&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;You may be a good fit if you&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have 5+ years of experience designing and operating enterprise networks, with focus on corporate/office environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are proficient with firewall management, routing protocols, VLANs, and layer 2/3 switching technologies&lt;/li&gt;
